body_html:
Not sure what to suggest.
Have you tried using a more recent version of TensorFlow? (e.g. 0.9 or 0.10rc ?)
Does the output of pip show protobuf look like this:

~/tensorflow.triage$ pip show protobuf
---
Name: protobuf
Version: 3.0.0b2
Location: /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages
Requires: six, setuptools

You're definitely running your tensorflow program with python 2.7 not accidentally using python 3 ? (in which case you'd need to pip3 install the protobuf package)

@martinwicke Any ideas?

body:
Not sure what to suggest.
Have you tried using a more recent version of TensorFlow?  (e.g. 0.9 or 0.10rc ?)
Does the output of `pip show protobuf` look like this:

```
~/tensorflow.triage$ pip show protobuf
---
Name: protobuf
Version: 3.0.0b2
Location: /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages
Requires: six, setuptools
```

You're definitely running your tensorflow program with python 2.7 not accidentally using python 3 ?  (in which case you'd need to **pip3** install the protobuf package)

@martinwicke Any ideas?
